description.plain:
Hykeem Jamaal Carter Jr. (born October 22, 2000), otherwise known as Baby Keem is a rapper, songwriter and producer from Las Vegas, Nevada.

He has produced for the likes of ScHoolboy Q, Jay Rock and Beyoncé and is affiliated with pgLang.

In an 2021 interview with Apple Music Keem spoke about how he came up with idea to call himself “Baby Keem”:

It started with me hearing a beat from someone I was a fan of for a long, long, long time — Cardo, and when I heard the beat I had a newfound confidence, I just felt like calling myself “Baby Keem”. I always joke around like “this is my name”, I always make fake nicknames for myself and things like that but, when I heard that beat it just sounded right, so I made a song called “Baby Keem”. After that that’s what it was.

He started gaining attention in 2018 with his projects Hearts and Darts and The Sound of Bad Habit. He got even more attention with his 2019 mixtape DIE FOR MY BITCH and his breakout single “ORANGE SODA” which went platinum.

In 2021 he released The Melodic Blue, his debut studio album with features from Kendrick Lamar, Travis Scott and Don Toliver.

He is Kendrick Lamar’s cousin and Keem is also part of Kendrick’s company pgLang.

songs.title: ORANGE SODA

description.plain:
“ORANGE SODA” is Baby Keem’s breakout hit. Released as a single from DIE FOR MY BITCH in June 2019, the song has quickly become a fan favorite and was certified platinum a year later.

The self-produced record finds Keem rapping about his “orange soda”—referring to the girl he’s attracted to. Keem talks to his significant other and addresses their relationship, which is troubled by her demands and by her friend’s interference.

A music video was released to complement the success of the single four months after the release of the song.

songs.title: ​vent

description.plain:
On ‘vent’ Baby Keem vents his anger into his verses. He raps about his fame and his displeasure of his friends who are now acting greedy and those acting like ‘rats’.

The fiery chorus is performed by his cousin Kendrick Lamar who also performs the ‘fade’ outro. Kendrick has a writing credit on this song for his contributions. He originally had his own verse in the first version of this song, the first half of his unreleased verse ended up being used on Kendrick Lamar’s song “N95”
The two cousins released the single family ties before the album drop.

The first version of the song was leaked on March 28th, 2020.

This track was also performed live before its official release on his new album The Melodic Blue. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WSWENElet-Y

songs.title: ​trademark usa

description.plain:
Initially appearing on the early versions of tracklists on what Keem had envisioned The Melodic Blue to be as “llc the dead,” this is the album’s opening track.

Interestingly, the song’s previous title itself was also teased in a shot for the “ORANGE SODA” music video.
